    <node id="topic:docsorter-pipeline">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">DocSorter sorting pipeline and stages</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">theme</data>
      <data key="d13">0.95</data>
      <data key="d14">["DocSorter", "sorting session", "sorting", "dating", "admissions", "file note", "QA", "clinician", "sorter", "stages"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "there's different stages within dark sorter so first it's the sorting and then it's the dating and then it's admissions and then there's the file note or the memo whenever they refer to memo it's also known as a file note but file note is actually the more the more commonly used one now um and then the qa so for each of these stages a clinician needs to be selected", "ts": 2132.7, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:ai-pre-processing">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">AI pre-processing: unitisation and classification</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:docsorter-pipeline</data>
      <data key="d13">0.95</data>
      <data key="d14">["pre-processing", "AI", "unitisation", "classification", "requires pre-processing", "Sally", "manual"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "all this is is whether the sorting session needs to be pre-processed pre-processed by ai um i'm sure diane explained that to you what we do with ai in the sorting session is we are doing the classification as well as the well obviously first do the unitization and then the classification so we we create put all the pages for the same document together in the right to order so that's your unitization and then your classification is once that is done they classify each document to whether to go to radiology cardiology maybe it's a clinical report", "ts": 2393.9, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:sorting-session-creation">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Creating a sorting session</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:docsorter-pipeline</data>
      <data key="d13">0.9</data>
      <data key="d14">["sorting session", "administrator", "client sort", "MedBrief sort", "Hempsons", "urgent", "due date", "pagination"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "the user would have to select and when i say user i mean the administrator may be administrator they would need to select if it's a client sorting session or a may be sorting session", "ts": 2074.4, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "in most cases it is a mid-week sorting session they can select if it's urgent when the due date is", "ts": 2106.1, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:records-page-structure">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Records page folder structure</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">theme</data>
      <data key="d13">0.9</data>
      <data key="d14">["records page", "folder tree", "viewer", "case documentation", "private folders", "unsorted records", "sorted records", "four parent folders"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "on the records page there's four main parent folders that will always be visible on this page we've got your records which is usually used for for sorted records then we've got case documentation as well as private folders", "ts": 2536.9, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Records tree: 000 - Index (index.pdf); A - Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust - Orla Grace Clayton; Case Documentation; Private Folders; Unsorted Records.", "ts": 2741.8, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:sorted-records-flow">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Sorted records flow from DocSorter to records page</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:records-page-structure</data>
      <data key="d13">0.9</data>
      <data key="d14">["sorted records", "push", "ZZZ folder", "cleanup", "unsorted records", "batches", "ops team"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "once records have been sorted that sorted set of records is then pushed to the records to the records folder um parent folder", "ts": 2614.8, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "when we push records from from doc sorter this is where it gets pushed to it actually gets pushed to it it has a funny folder name all of these folders will be in a single folder called zzz sorting session with the date", "ts": 2712.4, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:sorted-index-structure">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Sorted index hierarchy: trust, admission, records</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:records-page-structure</data>
      <data key="d13">0.9</data>
      <data key="d14">["sorted index", "trust", "medical institution", "admission", "event", "hierarchy", "patient", "duplicate", "date range", "page numbers", "updated", "bookmarks"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "the first level would be the trust or the medical institution where the documents are from the and then second level would be any events or uh usually events but specifically admissions if a person who was in in admitted to a hospital that would usually be grouped as well so documents for that mission will be grouped underneath and then you've got the records that apply to that that event or admission", "ts": 2847.3, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "it's a trust per um per patient by the way that's why you see two so you've got gp records same trust for all of grace clayton and then you've got the same trust for different patient which is the child elia elijah clayton", "ts": 2888.1, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:15"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:matter-dashboard-workspace">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Matter dashboard as shared workspace for admins and clients</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">theme</data>
      <data key="d13">0.8</data>
      <data key="d14">["matter dashboard", "workspace", "administrator", "client", "internal users", "visibility", "service requests", "progress tracking"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "so so yeah so this is sort of their workspace but it's also you know it's it's visible to both administrators and clients so clients can also see a lot of this and track according to the timelines", "ts": 2240.6, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13", "chapter:14"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:expert-folder-workflow">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Expert folders and suppressed invitation workflow</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:records-page-structure</data>
      <data key="d13">0.85</data>
      <data key="d14">["expert", "folder", "invitation", "suppressed invitation", "bell icon", "fee earner", "case documentation", "private folders", "users page"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "a lot of the time the fee earners what they do is they they create they invite an expert but then they also need to prepare the experts folder with whatever instructions that need to be in there maybe there's other expert reports that they want to share with that expert maybe there's additional documentation that they want to share with that expert so they want to prepare the folder first before the in the expert actually logs in and that's where the suppressed invitation comes in", "ts": 3054.2, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Manage invitations. Chantel Expert - Pending - Email expert@example.com.", "ts": 3168.3, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:16"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:auto-folder-creation">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Automatic folder creation on page view or expert invitation</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:records-page-structure</data>
      <data key="d13">0.8</data>
      <data key="d14">["folder creation", "auto", "viewer", "invited expert", "private folders", "case documentation", "expert not logged in yet"]</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "how these two work is anyone that views this page so if you had to come in you view this page a private folder will be created for you in both private folders as well as case documentation the this the same applies to um when an expert is invited then a folder will be they haven't seen the page yet but because they were invited a folder is created for them as well in both case documentation as well as private folders", "ts": 2548.3, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="topic:batch-document-upload">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Batch document upload and linking to sorting session</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">subtopic</data>
      <data key="d15">topic:docsorter-pipeline</data>
      <data key="d13">0.85</data>
      <data key="d14">["batch", "upload", "completed batch", "sorting session", "batches", "reorder", "document order", "number"]</data>
