      <data key="d1">Wizard has default pages plus conditional service-specific pages depending on first-page selections</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "these are the default pages that that everyone will see when they create a matter these pages here in the middle this is dependent on what services are selected on the first page here so if they for instance selects a chronology they will also get a chronology service page where they need to select the details there", "ts": 196.3, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "matter_creation flow diagram; Columns A B C D E F G H; services; matter detail; patient detail; records request; early case assessment; sort &amp; paginate; chronology; records collection; supporting documents; summary", "ts": 193.0, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:03"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The matter creation wizard always shows default pages (services, matter detail, patient detail, supporting documents, summary). Additional service-specific pages (records request, early case assessment, sort and paginate, chronology, records collection) are shown conditionally based on the services selected on the first page.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
