    <node id="claim:0021">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Billing code is optional except for Hampsons, where it is compulsory with a predefined drop-down</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "the billing code is optional um it's worth noting for defendant firms however and we've only got two defendant firms which is kennedy's and the other one i think is hampsons", "ts": 794.2, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "what that means for hampsons is that this field would be compulsory and then they will have a drop-down list of predefined billing codes that they can choose from so that's that's the only difference", "ts": 820.4, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:05"]</data>
      <data key="d20">Billing code is an optional field for most clients. For defendant firm Hampsons it is compulsory, and Hampsons users see a predefined drop-down of codes rather than a free-text field. Kennedy's is the other defendant firm but has not set up predefined codes.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
