    <node id="claim:0061">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">The requires-pre-processing flag triggers AI unitisation then classification</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d20">The 'requires pre-processing' checkbox on a sorting session triggers AI pre-processing: first unitisation (grouping pages for the same document in the correct order) and then classification (categorising each document by type, e.g. radiology, cardiology, clinical report, nurses notes).</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d25">2393.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "all this is is whether the sorting session needs to be pre-processed pre-processed by ai um i'm sure diane explained that to you what we do with ai in the sorting session is we are doing the classification as well as the well obviously first do the unitization and then the classification so we we create put all the pages for the same document together in the right to order so that's your unitization and then your classification is once that is done they classify each document to whether to go to radiology cardiology maybe it's a clinical report a nurses report that type of thing nurses notes etc so that's what the ai does and this is what this this check box um indicates if i deselect it it means that it will all be a manual unitization and classification process by the actual clinician", "ts": 2393.9, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
